Umar Muhammed, Lafia The Nasarawa State Governor, Abdullahi Sule, has said there was no rift between him and his predecessor, the senator representing Nasarawa South, Umaru Al-Makura He said stories on the social media about a rift between them were mere fabrications. The governor spoke on Monady during a thank-you visit of Bari Bare nationality from the Lafia Local Government Area of the state to appreciate him for appointing one of their sons, Muhammed Ubandoma, as Secretary to the Nasarawa State Government. He said, “I am from a royal family and we are not known for treachery and I have respect for elders. I respect the former governor, Umaru Al-Makura, and will continue to do so as long as I live.” Al-Makura had also refuted that there was any rift between him and Sule, insisting that the incubent governor and himself had  known each other for long. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 